</div><div id="c4047">

<p>Some possibilities:</p>

<ol>
<li>I misread/misremembered the hand-written notation.</li>
<li>It wasn&#8217;t actually the Robber&#8217;s Cave experiment but something just like it &#8212; a reproduction, perhaps?</li>
<li>The handwritten bit was there to fool us.</li>
</ol>

<p class="posted">posted by <a target="_blank" title="http://www.aaronsw.com/" href="http://notabug.com/mt/gorsnikat.cgi?__mode=red;id=4047">Aaron Swartz</a> at February 27, 2005 01:56 PM <a href="001593#c4047">#</a></p>

</div><div id="c4081">

<p>I would think the classes will get better, but yeah&#8212;you&#8217;re not exactly getting your money&#8217;s worth.  I guess some of it is access to great minds&#8230;when then pawn you off onto a TV program.  <em>shrug</em>  You alternately make me feel bad I didn&#8217;t go there and then not so bad that I didn&#8217;t waste the money.:7</p>

<p>As for the hives, you may want to look into the possibility you&#8217;re allergic to something in the cookie.  My son is allergic to peanuts and reacts very similarly&#8212;seems to show up on his hands first even if he ate it, then down to the stomach.  I&#8217;m telling you, I&#8217;d seriously look at the possibility. Always good to know what you&#8217;re allergic to.</p>

<p>As for the reason for the handwritten note on the Robber&#8217;s Cave thing, I&#8217;m going with #3, but I&#8217;m a cynical bastard.</p>

